f Native American translation and the growing modernist concern for a "native" sense of the "makings" of American verse. This fascinating work represents a major new effort in understanding American and Native American literature, spirituality, and culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAmerican poetryxIndian authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican poetryxIndian influences. 0aIndians in literature. 0aIndians of North AmericaxIntellectual life. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  aamerican indian.  aamerican literature.  aamerican poetry.  aamerican verse.  abible.  abiblical.  acontemporary poetry.  aculture.  aethnicity.  aethnopoetics.  afree verse.  agender studies.  agender.  agreenwich village.  aindigenous people.  aindigenous.  alakota.  aliterary analysis.  aliterary criticism.  alost garden.  amodernist.  amythology.  anative american literature.  anative american.  anative literature.  anew world.  apoetic criticism.  apoetic verse.  apoetry analysis.  apoetry studies.  arenaissance.  aspirituality.  atranslation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052021890140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520922952?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520922952423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520922952/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles